reviews.review_text: Dentist the Menace Folks, this as good as it gets......I am blown away by this show...the 2nd set is AMAZING!!!  Just take some time and go through the whole motions of this one.......WOW!!!

tight clean sound strong show with beautiful soundboard quality.

Scarlet Fire is fantastic and
the eleven is beautifully jammed out

namaste

Sick, sick, sick... This one is a rager.  WOW.  Did I say WOW? I meant to say WOWWWWWWW!!!
Second set is simply amazing.
Really powerful sound - big and fat and played like they mean it.
Hidden Gem This one's a hidden gem IMO.  Scarlet Fire is a real scortcher!  Birdsong is no slouch either.  Glad I gave this one a try, I'm likin' it!
NOT BAD That guy Jerry could sing pretty well, too.

one the highlights of the Brent era Rooster into Bossman? A lively It's All Over Now, specially with Brents solo stealing the spotlight. A tear jerkin' He's Gone, with a mesmerizing ending, almost resembles a Tribal chant, calling to the Gods. An awesome rarity "Day At the Dentist" which 3 minutes into you can't tell if its still the Dead, you are listening to, or an Ambient music channel on satellite TV. Heavy stuff from the greatest band of all Time!
I have a dentist. His name is Crentist.

real festivities I enjoyed the vibe at the Greeks and Oakland 1981.
Special mention for 12/26: All Over Now, Fire, He's Gone, Peter and the space!
4 stars is the max after '73, because a curve will not necessarily be discerned.
Nice Start To The New Year's Run Highlights: Big Boss Man, He's Gone, Oakland Jam
Thanks WOW what an amazing show! Thanks for the Stream! absolutely wow!
